news.title: West Bengal RERA is now functional: Sandipan Mukherjee, Chairman
news.para: "The WBRERA is now in place and we have very recently commenced functioning. The website is expected to be operational within a fortnight," said Sandipan Mukherjee, who assumed charge as WBRERA chairman.

news.title: Delhi's GPRA colonies project to stretch to 2025-end
news.para: The housing and urban affairs ministry has informed the Lok Sabha that so far residential projects at Mohammadpur and Thyagraj Nagar have been completed.

news.title: No multipoint connections yet, power to AIMS Angel Golf Avenue 2 cut for seven hours
news.para: ​The move followed non-compliance by the builder with the March 31 directions of the UP Electricity Regulatory Commission (UPERC), seeking conversion to multipoint connections or deciding to retain single point connections with the consent of 51% of the residents.

news.title: No amenities at Lucknow development body's Deepshikha Apartment irk residents
news.para: Residents narrated their woes during ‘Janta Adalat’, the grievance redressal camp organised by LDA at its headquarters in Gomtinagar, on Thursday.

news.title: World of plots – A True Investment Opportunity
Nagpur: Show cause notices to 10 AMCs over poor property tax collection
news.para: Against a target of Rs 300 crore set by municipal commissioner and administrator Radhakrishnan B, so far, the 10 zones of NMC have collected only Rs 127 crore.

news.title: Chandigarh civic body seals four properties in three days over tax dues
news.para: The list of commercial tax defaulters has been prepared and approved by officers concerned. Sources said that more such properties would be sealed in the days to come.

news.title: Chhattisgarh consumer court orders builder to refund applicant's money along with fine
news.para: The applicant had booked an apartment in the under-construction Anandam Apartment on November 22, 2014 and paid Rs four lakh in advance. The applicant paid a total of Rs 25,34,876 in different installments.

news.title: Mumbai: EOW nabs builder Jagdish Ahuja for Rs 27 crore cheating case
news.para: DCP Sangramsinh Nishandar, said, "We have detained Jagdish Ahuja after working on information for a few days. He is involved in three cases registered with EOW."

news.title: Super-rich to pay higher property transfer fees in Ahmedabad
news.para: ​According to the revenue committee of the AMC, it will charge 0.1% to 0.2% of the sale deed value as property ownership transfer fees for residential properties depending on the value slab.

news.title: NPCL send notices to nine builders about multi-point or single point connections
news.para: Housing societies in Greater Noida and Greater Noida West, including Alpha Homes, Ace City, Samridhi Grand, Panch-sheel Greens 2, Panchsheel Hy-nish, Divyansh Flora, Mahagun Mywoods 6th Avenue, Gaur City 1 and Pristine Avenue, have received these notices.

news.title: Bengaluru: Court orders stay in PNB Housing, Mantri-Webcity case
news.para: At the hearing on December 2, the Division Bench made a categorical note that there are certain arguable issues in the order dated September 14 that requires consideration and admitted the Writ appeal.

news.title: PMLA case: No predicate offence, Ara Developers' director cleared
news.para: In August, the ED had submitted a chargesheet against Amit Bhosale, his company Ara Developers and two others in a case related to the purchase of a plot in Pune by allegedly manipulating rules.

news.title: Court orders to freeze bank accounts of Godrej Air on funds irregularity charge
news.para: ​The project, which is being developed by Godrej Properties Limited (GPL) in collaboration with Orris Infrastructure Private Limited (OIPL), is spread over 10-acre land and has 500 units in five towers.

news.title: Maharashtra RERA issues order on fixed sale deed clauses
news.para: The RERA Act mandates that promoters upload, along with the application for registration of a real estate project, the proforma of the agreement for sale.
